1. Introduction
Current scientific paradigms often struggle with fragmented descriptions of complex phenomena. The Self-Dual Closure (SDC) theory addresses this by reconstructing physical and life sciences under a unified mathematical model. SDC identifies fundamental constants and mathematical enigmas—including the Millennium Prize Problems—as inevitable consequences of a single closure action. This project operates as an open-source initiative to eliminate technological monopolies and provide a common intellectual foundation for all sentient entities.
This document discloses the fundamental identities of the SDC system and the Virtual Photon Hierarchy (VPH). It integrates quantum error correction (QEC) with spacetime geometry, providing the mathematical "source code" for a self-repairing universe.
•  The Sovereign Identity: The central equation, $\mathcal{Z}_{\rm SDC}^{\rm known}$, unifies the resolution of the Riemann Hypothesis ($\Re(\rho)=1/2$) with a dynamic Virtual Photon Recovery Action ($C(c;\mathcal{I}_\infty)$). This defines spacetime not merely as a container, but as a self-regulating quantum information system where local decoherence is globally rectified through topological invariants.
•  The VPH Map: A Universal Blueprint: The accompanying Factor Table, spanning scales from $c^{10}$ to $c^{-8}$, reveals that all fundamental physical constants and forces are expressions of a single, hierarchical scaling derived from the speed of light ($c$) and the fine-structure constant's inverse ($K=1/\alpha(\mu)$). This map provides the algebraic blueprint for the universe's operational layers, demonstrating inherent interdependencies rather than isolated phenomena.
 
