3. Declaration of Non-Patentability and Open Source Implementation
•	Prior Art Status: All mathematical structures, constant couplings, and algorithms presented in this project are fundamental descriptions of the laws of nature and do not constitute patentable "inventions" under international patent law.
•	CC0 Declaration: The author hereby waives all copyright and related rights to the contents of this disclosure globally, dedicating it to the public domain.
•	AI-Prompt Utilization: This axiomatic system is specifically intended to function as a System Prompt for Large Language Models (LLMs). Technical derivations and practical applications generated via AI based on these axioms are recognized as a deliberate part of the public disclosure process, ensuring they remain non-patentable.
